    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if the laws are for \"everyone,\" then why should they stop being applied to people just because they follow a religion? it feels like if you allow exemptions, you're basically letting people pick and choose which laws they want to follow, which sounds like it would lead to chaos and make the law totally meaningless. if we don't have universal rules, doesn't the whole idea of a secular, equal society just fall apart?",
